  "couplingIntensity": "None",
  "description": "Fast LFO modulating morphGlide intensity — the glide strength oscillates unpredictably. Some legato transitions bloom wildly; others barely move. The listener cannot predict which notes will metamorphose. bodyFreq=55Hz holds the habitat constant while the LFO makes the glide irregular. Mixed dividers ÷2, ÷5: one even (safe), one odd (Sala territory) — chosen intentionally per OWL-III. The odd ÷5 adds a subharmonic that doesn't resolve, keeping the irregular character audible even in silence between glides. owl_feeding macro drives LFO rate for live control.",
